article.headline: Denver 55, Montana State 53
article.story: DENVER (AP) -- Erik Benzel hit a jumper with 2.3 seconds left to give the University of Denver a 55-53 victory over Montana State on Wednesday night. Brett Starkey had 14 points for Denver (2-2). Rodney Billups had 13 and Antonio Porch had 12 off the bench. Benzel, who was averaging 17 points going into Wednesday's game, had missed his eight previous shots before the game-winner. He finished with just three. Frank Brown had 18 points and Jason Erickson 14 for Montana State (3-2). Denver shot 37 percent overall and just 28 percent in the first half. Montana State shot 33 percent overall. Porch gave Denver its first second-half lead after subbing for Carvell McAllister after McAllister's third foul three minutes into the second half.
